  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ECHO NUTRITION 2018</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will contribute to the prevention of under nutrition and also to prevent very poor households from developing harmful strategies, and allow these households to protect or even maintain their productive assets. The nutritional approach, through sensitization and training, the involvement of all socio-economic groups, the production and use of porridges based on local products, is a guarantee of well-being, development and normal growth. children.
ECHO 2018 is an emergency response to food and nutrition insecurity in Seno area with three components: 1) securing the livelihoods of 1350 very poor households through unconditional cash transfers (1 Result ); 2) improving the nutritional status of 1000 children at risk of malnutrition through the distribution of enriched flour accompanied by awareness sessions</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This action will prevent the degradation and improve the nutritional status of children at risk as well as improve the food consumption of households that will be in deficit of survival and protection by the end of November 2018. For this, the project provides to support during 4 months of welding 1350 households TP with child at risk through food aid, in the form of unconditional transfer, cash or coupons, and fortified infant flour. The cash / coupon will be distributed during the 3 months of peak welding, up to 32,500 CFA per month, households with children at risk of 0-23 months.
Three strategic components for the emergency response to food and nutrition insecurity:
- Strengthening social protection of vulnerable households in securing livelihoods;
- Improving nutritional status of children from very poor households aged 0 - 23 months;
- Advocacy for the institutionalization of social safety nets;</narrative>
  </description>
